From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Add source tree include paths for Stage0 C compilation

When cross-version bootstrapping (e.g., using GHC 9.6.7 to build GHC 9.2.8),
Stage0 utilities like hsc2hs have C sources (cbits/utils.c) that include
GHC headers like HsBase.h and HsFFI.h.

The original code only adds -Iincludes for notStage0 builds, assuming
Stage0 would use bootstrap headers. But when compiling source tree code
at Stage0, we need access to the source tree's headers.

Without this patch, the build fails with:
  Error, file does not exist and no rule available:
    HsFFI.h

This patch:
- Adds -Iincludes for all stages (not just notStage0)
- Adds -Ilibraries/base/include for packages that need base's C headers

--- a/hadrian/src/Settings/Builders/Common.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Settings/Builders/Common.hs
@@ -27,7 +27,11 @@ cIncludeArgs = do
     depDirs <- getContextData depIncludeDirs
     stage <- getStage
     libPath <- expr $ stageLibPath stage
-    mconcat [ notStage0 ||^ package compiler ? arg "-Iincludes"
+    -- Always add source tree includes for packages with C sources needing
+    -- GHC headers. This is essential for cross-version bootstrap where
+    -- Stage0 utilities like hsc2hs need HsFFI.h and HsBase.h.
+    mconcat [ arg "-Iincludes"
+            , arg "-Ilibraries/base/include"
             , arg $ "-I" ++ libPath
             , arg $ "-I" ++ path
             -- Add @incDirs@ in the build directory, since some files generated
